  "root_text": {
    "iti62:0.1": "Itivuttaka 62 ",
    "iti62:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti62:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti62:0.4": "Indriyasutta ",
    "iti62:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti62:2.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni. ",
    "iti62:2.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "iti62:2.3": "Anaññātaññassāmītindriyaṁ, aññindriyaṁ, aññātāvindriyaṁ—",
    "iti62:2.4": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi indriyānī”ti. ",
    "iti62:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti62:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti62:3.1": "“Sekhassa sikkhamānassa, ",
    "iti62:3.2": "ujumaggānusārino; ",
    "iti62:3.3": "Khayasmiṁ paṭhamaṁ ñāṇaṁ, ",
    "iti62:3.4": "tato aññā anantarā. ",
    "iti62:4.1": "Tato aññāvimuttassa, ",
    "iti62:4.2": "ñāṇaṁ ve hoti tādino; ",
    "iti62:4.3": "Akuppā me vimuttīti, ",
    "iti62:4.4": "bhavasaṁyojanakkhayā. ",
    "iti62:5.1": "Sa ve indriyasampanno, ",
    "iti62:5.2": "santo santipade rato; ",
    "iti62:5.3": "Dhāreti antimaṁ dehaṁ, ",
    "iti62:5.4": "jetvā māraṁ savāhinin”ti. ",
    "iti62:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti62:6.2": "Tatiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti62:0.1": "So It Was Said 62 ",
    "iti62:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti62:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti62:0.4": "Faculties ",
    "iti62:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti62:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three faculties. ",
    "iti62:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti62:2.3": "The faculty of understanding that one’s enlightenment is imminent. The faculty of enlightenment. The faculty of one who is enlightened. ",
    "iti62:2.4": "These are the three faculties.” ",
    "iti62:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti62:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti62:3.1": "“As a trainee trains, ",
    "iti62:3.2": "following the straight road, ",
    "iti62:3.3": "first they know about ending; ",
    "iti62:3.4": "enlightenment follows in the same lifetime. ",
    "iti62:4.1": "Then the knowledge comes ",
    "iti62:4.2": "to such a one, freed through enlightenment, ",
    "iti62:4.3": "with the end of the fetters of continued existence: ",
    "iti62:4.4": "‘My freedom is unshakable.’ ",
    "iti62:5.1": "Accomplished in the faculties, ",
    "iti62:5.2": "peaceful, in love with the state of peace, ",
    "iti62:5.3": "they bear their final body, ",
    "iti62:5.4": "having vanquished Māra with his legions.” ",
    "iti62:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti62:5.1": "Sa ve → sace (sya-all) "
  },
